  "body": "The following code snippet was broken in Helm v2.8.2 due to the connection timeout logic introduced:\r\n\r\n```\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"log\"\r\n\r\n\t\"k8s.io/helm/pkg/helm\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nconst (\r\n\ttillerHost = \"127.0.0.1:44134\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\r\n\thelmClient := helm.NewClient(helm.Host(tillerHost))\r\n\t_, err := helmClient.ListReleases()\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatalf(\"err: %v\", err)\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is due to https://github.com/kubernetes/helm/blob/250d25fdceaf5546f29228f3711cedd8d6776fcd/pkg/helm/client.go#L326, which before had a hardcoded 5 second timeout. Because the above snippet does not specify a timeout value via [Helm's options](https://github.com/kubernetes/helm/blob/c5f2174f264554c62278c0695d58f250d3e207c8/cmd/helm/helm.go#L269), the client immediately fails with \"err: context deadline exceeded\".",
